## Error Handling Rules
- Backend: Always throw `HttpException` with a descriptive message and correct HTTP status
- Frontend: Wrap all API calls in try/catch, display user-friendly error messages
- Handle these specific cases:
  - `409 Conflict` → "This time slot is no longer available"
  - `400 Bad Request` → Show Zod validation errors to user
  - `401 Unauthorized` → Redirect to login
  - `500 Internal Server Error` → "Something went wrong, please try again"
- Never show stack traces or DB error messages to the user

---

## Authentication Rules
- Use JWT access tokens (short-lived: 15min) + refresh tokens (7 days)
- Store access token in memory (React state), refresh token in HttpOnly cookie
- Protect all booking mutation endpoints with `JwtAuthGuard`
- `GET /bookings/available` is public (no auth required)
- Implement `POST /auth/login`, `POST /auth/register`, `POST /auth/refresh`

---

## Concurrency & Double Booking Prevention
- Use PostgreSQL advisory locks OR `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` inside a transaction
- Check availability and insert in a single transaction:
  ```ts
  await db.transaction(async (tx) => {
    const existing = await tx.select()...where(eq(bookings.timeSlot, slot)).for('update')
    if (existing.length > 0) throw new ConflictException(...)
    await tx.insert(bookings).values(...)
  })
  ```

