## Testing Rules
- Unit tests: Jest for NestJS services (mock DB layer)
- Integration tests: Supertest for API endpoints
- E2E tests: Playwright for critical booking flow
- Test file naming: `*.spec.ts` for unit, `*.e2e-spec.ts` for E2E
- Minimum coverage targets: Services 80%, Controllers 70%

---

## Code Style
- Use `async/await` — never `.then().catch()` chains
- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals
- All exported functions/classes must have JSDoc comments
- No magic strings — define constants in packages/shared
- Prettier + ESLint must pass before committing
- Commit messages: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `test:` prefixes

